
Overview of noun pant

The noun pant has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                         
1. pant -- (the noise made by a short puff of steam (as from an engine))
2. trouser, pant -- ((usually in the plural) a garment extending from the waist to the knee or ankle, covering each leg separately; "he had a sharp crease in his trousers")
3. gasp, pant -- (a short labored intake of breath with the mouth open; "she gave a gasp and fainted")

Overview of verb pant

The verb pant has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (9) pant, puff, gasp, heave -- (breathe noisily, as when one is exhausted; "The runners reached the finish line, panting heavily")
2. (1) pant -- (utter while panting, as if out of breath)
